headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 22 points and the Toronto Raptors rallied from four 9-point first quarter deficits to roll past the Charlotte Hornets 120-100 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 22, leads Raptors over Hornets 120-100

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler scored 18 of his 27 points in the fourth quarter and the Miami Heat avoided an embarrassing loss by rallying to beat the hapless Detroit Pistons 118-105 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler leads Heat to late win against Pistons, 118-105

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 43 points, his fourth straight 40-point game, to lead the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 117-113 victory over the Orlando Magic on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 43 to lead Cavs to 117-113 win over Magic

headlines.description: — The Milwaukee Bucks were eliminated last season in a Game 7 on the road.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo's triple-double lifts Bucks over Wizards

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 23 points, Karl-Anthony Towns had 22 points, 14 rebounds and five assists, and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Brooklyn Nets 107-102 on Tuesday night to snap a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards, Towns help Wolves edge Nets 107-102, end skid at 3

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid earned the highest stamp of approval from coach Doc Rivers after the All-Star center blistered Boston for his third 50-point game of the season and carried the 76ers on his beat-up, 7-foot frame to victory.
— Bogdan Bogdanovic scored 26 points and the Atlanta Hawks overcame the loss of top scorer Trae Young to beat the Chicago Bulls 123-105 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bogdanovic's 26 lead Young-less Hawks past Bulls 123-105

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 32 points, six others scored in double figures and the last-place Houston Rockets prevented the Denver Nuggets from clinching the No. 1 seed in the Western Conference with a 124-103 victory in their home finale on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets prevent Nuggets from clinching West with 124-103 win

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 30 points and keyed a fourth-quarter rally, Ja Morant added 23 points and nine assists and the Memphis Grizzlies defeated the short-handed Portland Trail Blazers 119-109 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane's late burst leads Grizzlies past Trail Blazers 119-109

events.name: Sacramento Kings at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Sacramento rookie Keegan Murray could be the face of the Kings' remarkable reversal of fortune.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings beat Pelicans 121-103 to clinch Pacific Division title

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — LeBron James missed a potential game-winning layup on the final play of regulation. Given a second chance, he delivered.
headlines.shortLinkText: James' game-winner lifts Lakers past Jazz in OT

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — These second-half comebacks are becoming a thing for the Golden State Warriors, much like those old third-quarter surges that used to define this bunch.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry, Poole combine for 64 as Warriors beat Thunder 136-125

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 27 points and the Phoenix Suns never trailed, beating the depleted San Antonio Spurs 115-94 on Tuesday night to clinch a playoff spot.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns clinch playoff spot, rout injury-riddled Spurs 115-94
